&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of product design experience, ideally in B2B SaaS or AI-focused roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2-3 years operating at a Staff / Principal level, with proven ownership of complex initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong portfolio showcasing your ability to create clear, user-focused products and strategies. Demonstrating both the impact on user experience and business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A deep understanding of AI and AI design tooling and the ability to show you’re leading the charge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience working closely with cross-functional teams, including product management, UX design, and engineering, to deliver seamless content solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of UX practices, information architecture, and user-centred design methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to articulate the value of design and collaborate effectively ac

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Strategic Accounts team’s mission is to make Miro the nerve center for innovation inside the world’s largest companies. We partner with Fortune 500 and Global 2000 enterprises to help them accelerate product development, improve cross-functional alignment, and transform how teams move from strategy to execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team sits at the center of Miro’s evolution from a collaboration product to an AI-powered innovation workspace. Our Strategic AEs operate as account CEOs, leading cross-functional account teams across Solution Engineering, Customer Success, Value Advisory, Professional Services, Product, Marketing, Partners, and executive leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
